- 'feature' and 'bug' are types of labels that can be assigned to issues;
- 'closed' status indicates that the issue has been resolved or is no longer open;
- A commit is a change or update made to the codebase.

- 'blossoms' refer to comments;
- 'branches' refer to issues;
- 'first tree' refers to the first project in the list that has at least one comment.

- "Issues" can be thought of as tasks or problems that need to be addressed in a project;
- "Commits" represent changes or solutions made to address these issues;
- Ranking by the number of commits is akin to ranking by the amount of effort or attention given to each issue.

- 'Project Alpha' is the name of a specific project in the database;
- 'John Doe' is the name of a specific actor who can create issues;
- The difference in days is calculated using Julian day numbers to ensure accuracy.

- A project can have multiple issues and labels;
- The hierarchy of projects is built based on the absence or presence of issues;
- The total count is the sum of issues and labels for each project.

- 'Top three' refers to the projects with the highest average body length for issues;
- 'Open projects' are those whose issues are currently not closed or in progress;
- 'Overall average comments' is the average number of comments across all issues in the database.

- 'Issues' refer to tasks or problems that need to be addressed within a project;
- 'Comments' are discussions or notes added to an issue by team members or stakeholders;
- 'Project' is a collection of issues and tasks that are managed together.

- 'Active issues' refers to issues where the project is not archived (`is_archived = 0`);
- 'Thorns of bugs' and 'seeds of features' are metaphors for 'bug' and 'feature' labels, respectively;
- 'Burdened by the thorns of bugs' means the issue has at least one 'bug' label (`bug_count > 0`);
- 'Not the seeds of features' means the issue has no 'feature' label (`feature_count = 0`);
- 'Gardener who planted them' refers to the creator of the issue (`creator_name`).

- "blossoms" refers to projects;
- "closed petals" refers to closed issues;
- "time to wither" refers to the time taken for issues to be closed;
- "gardeners" refers to actors involved in the issues.

sql:
SELECT title
FROM issues
WHERE comments > (SELECT AVG(comments) FROM issues);
